    <note type="dates"><date>1812–88</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Italian chemist. Studied chemistry in Turin, Paris, and Giessen. Shared a laboratory with Alfred Nobel in Paris. Discovered nitroglycerin (called "pyroglycerine" by Sobrero) in 1846, but condemned the substance as too dangerous for use.</p></note>
